HB 925 Original 2026 Regular Session Henry
Abstract: Provides clarification relative to the practice of audiology and speech-language
pathology.
Present law provides for the practice of audiology to also include audiology services for
disorders of the vestibular system upon referral of a physician.
Proposed law removes the referral of a physician provision.
Proposed law permits audiologists to order cultures, blood work testing, and radiographic
imaging solely related to the auditory or vestibular conditions in the human ear; and to order
and perform in-office non-radiographic testing for the purposes hearing and balance disorder
evaluations.
Proposed law prohibits audiologists from performing surgery using instruments including
a laser, scalpel, needle, cautery, cryoprobe, or suture, in which human tissue is modified or
otherwise permanently altered by mechanical, laser, ionizing radiation, ultrasound, or other
means.
